<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>California Residential Lease Agreement</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;
      font-size: 11pt;
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: #000;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 20px;
    }
    .header {
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 30px;
      border-bottom: 2px solid #000;
      padding-bottom: 20px;
    }
    .header h1 {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: 18pt;
      font-weight: bold;
    }
    .section {
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }
    .section-title {
      font-weight: bold;
      font-size: 12pt;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
      text-decoration: underline;
    }
    .info-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 15px;
      margin-bottom: 15px;
    }
    .info-item {
      margin-bottom: 8px;
    }
    .info-label {
      font-weight: bold;
      display: inline-block;
      min-width: 120px;
    }
    .tenants-list {
      margin: 15px 0;
    }
    .tenant-item {
      margin-bottom: 10px;
      padding: 10px;
      background-color: #f5f5f5;
      border-left: 3px solid #333;
    }
    .signature-section {
      margin-top: 40px;
      page-break-inside: avoid;
    }
    .signature-line {
      border-top: 1px solid #000;
      margin-top: 60px;
      width: 300px;
      display: inline-block;
    }
    .terms {
      margin-top: 30px;
    }
    .terms ol {
      margin-left: 20px;
    }
    .terms li {
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }
    .ca-notice {
      background-color: #fff3cd;
      border: 2px solid #ffc107;
      padding: 15px;
      margin: 20px 0;
      border-radius: 5px;
    }
    @media print {
      body {
        padding: 0;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="header">
    <h1>CALIFORNIA RESIDENTIAL LEASE AGREEMENT</h1>
    <p><strong>{{organizationName}}</strong></p>
  </div>

  <div class="ca-notice">
    <strong>CALIFORNIA-SPECIFIC NOTICE:</strong> This lease is subject to California Civil Code and local rent control ordinances. 
    Tenant has the right to receive a copy of this lease agreement.
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-title">1. PARTIES</div>
    <p>
      This Lease Agreement ("Lease") is entered into on <strong>{{generatedDate}}</strong>, 
      between <strong>{{organizationName}}</strong> ("Landlord") and the following tenant(s) ("Tenant"):
    </p>
    <div class="tenants-list">
      {{#each tenants}}
      <div class="tenant-item">
        <strong>{{firstName}} {{lastName}}</strong>
        {{#if isPrimary}}<em>(Primary Tenant)</em>{{/if}}<br>
        {{#if email}}Email: {{email}}{{/if}}{{#if phone}} | Phone: {{phone}}{{/if}}
      </div>
      {{/each}}
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-title">2. PROPERTY</div>
    <div class="info-grid">
      <div class="info-item">
        <span class="info-label">Property:</span> {{propertyName}}
      </div>
      <div class="info-item">
        <span class="info-label">Address:</span> {{propertyAddress}}
      </div>
      <div class="info-item">
        <span class="info-label">Unit:</span> {{unitName}}
      </div>
      <div class="info-item">
        <span class="info-label">State:</span> California (CA)
      </div>
      {{#if bedrooms}}
      <div class="info-item">
        <span class="info-label">Bedrooms:</span> {{bedrooms}}
      </div>
      {{/if}}
      {{#if bathrooms}}
      <div class="info-item">
        <span class="info-label">Bathrooms:</span> {{bathrooms}}
      </div>
      {{/if}}
      {{#if squareFeet}}
      <div class="info-item">
        <span class="info-label">Square Feet:</span> {{squareFeet}}
      </div>
      {{/if}}
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-title">3. TERM</div>
    <p>
      The term of this Lease shall commence on <strong>{{date startDate}}</strong> and shall terminate on 
      <strong>{{date endDate}}</strong>, unless sooner terminated in accordance with the terms of this Lease.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-title">4. RENT</div>
    <div class="info-grid">
      <div class="info-item">
        <span class="info-label">Monthly Rent:</span> {{currency rentAmount}}
      </div>
      <div class="info-item">
        <span class="info-label">Rent Due Date:</span> Day {{rentDueDay}} of each month
      </div>
      {{#if depositAmount}}
      <div class="info-item">
        <span class="info-label">Security Deposit:</span> {{currency depositAmount}}
      </div>
      {{/if}}
    </div>
    <p>
      Rent shall be due and payable in advance on the {{rentDueDay}} day of each month during the term of this Lease. 
      If rent is not received by the {{rentDueDay}} day of the month, Tenant shall be in default of this Lease.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>California Law:</strong> Under California Civil Code Section 1947, rent is due on the date specified in this lease. 
      Late fees may not exceed reasonable costs incurred by the landlord.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="section terms">
    <div class="section-title">5. TERMS AND CONDITIONS</div>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <strong>Use of Premises:</strong> Tenant shall use the premises solely as a private residence and for no other purpose.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Maintenance:</strong> Tenant shall maintain the premises in good condition and promptly notify Landlord of any needed repairs. 
        Landlord is responsible for maintaining the premises in habitable condition per California Civil Code Section 1941.1.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Alterations:</strong> Tenant shall not make any alterations, additions, or improvements to the premises without Landlord's prior written consent.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Utilities:</strong> Tenant shall be responsible for all utilities unless otherwise specified in writing.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Pets:</strong> No pets are allowed on the premises without Landlord's prior written consent.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Security Deposit:</strong> The security deposit shall be held by Landlord in accordance with California Civil Code Section 1950.5. 
        The deposit may be applied to any damages, unpaid rent, or other charges owed by Tenant. 
        Within 21 days of termination, Landlord shall provide an itemized statement of any deductions.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Rent Control:</strong> This property may be subject to local rent control ordinances. 
        Tenant is advised to check with local housing authorities for applicable regulations.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Default:</strong> If Tenant fails to pay rent or breaches any term of this Lease, Landlord may terminate this Lease 
        in accordance with California Civil Code Section 1946 and pursue all available remedies.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Governing Law:</strong> This Lease shall be governed by the laws of the State of California.
      </li>
    </ol>
  </div>

  <div class="signature-section">
    <p>IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the parties have executed this Lease as of the date first written above.</p>
    
    <div style="margin-top: 40px;">
      <div style="display: inline-block; width: 45%; vertical-align: top;">
        <p><strong>LANDLORD:</strong></p>
        <p>{{organizationName}}</p>
        <div class="signature-line"></div>
        <p style="margin-top: 5px; font-size: 9pt;">Signature</p>
        <div class="signature-line" style="margin-top: 20px;"></div>
        <p style="margin-top: 5px; font-size: 9pt;">Date</p>
      </div>
      
      <div style="display: inline-block; width: 45%; vertical-align: top; margin-left: 5%;">
        <p><strong>TENANT(S):</strong></p>
        {{#each tenants}}
        <p>{{firstName}} {{lastName}}</p>
        <div class="signature-line"></div>
        <p style="margin-top: 5px; font-size: 9pt;">Signature</p>
        <div class="signature-line" style="margin-top: 20px;"></div>
        <p style="margin-top: 5px; font-size: 9pt;">Date</p>
        {{#unless @last}}<br><br>{{/unless}}
        {{/each}}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>

